                                "text": "Each version of Smalltalk was created as a simulation in an earlier version Smalltalk. It was particularly easy to make a new functioning class heirarchy along side the existing one. Smalltalk-76 was quite a bit different from ST-74, and it was vital to build one inside of ST-74. New data formats for objects were easy to simulate. Dan Ingalls got as far as running a simulated version of the compiler for ST-76 to verify that it would work once we \u201ccrossed the bridge\u201d to the new system."
